Program: Discovery
Title: Learning to Speak
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrw98
Last Broadcast Date: 03 October 1994
How do children learn to speak, and why do some learn more slowly that others? Also, manipulating atoms using a scanning and tunnelling microscope and Nobel Prize winning physicist Murray Gell-Mann on the link between the laws of physics and the complexity of the natural world. Presented by Dee Palmer. Show less